any good chicken recipes i recently changed my diet with my doctors permission to eat chicken only i was wondering if anyone had any good recipes for chicken i don't mind if it is chicken breast a whole chicken drumbsticks you name it i also don't mind if it takes a long time or has a lot of ingredients thank you so much in advance it really helps here are some of my favorite chicken recipes baked buttermilk chicken chicken cut up c flour tsp salt tsp pepper cups buttermilk cup butter melted can cream of chicken soup mix flour salt and pepper dip chicken in cup buttermilk and roll in flour mixture place melted butter in baking pan put chicken in pan skin side down and bake minutes at degrees turn and bake minutes mix soup and remaining cup of buttermilk and pour over chicken bake additional minutes or until golden brown makes a delicious gravy pecan chicken boneless skinless chicken breasts cup honey cup dijon mustard cup pecans finely chopped place each piece of chicken between sheets of wax paper flatten to inch thickness using meat mallet or rolling pin set aside combine honey and mustard spread on both sides of chicken and dredge chicken in chopped pecans arrange chicken in a shallow baking dish slightly greased bake at degrees for minutes or until tender serves stove top easy cheesy chicken bake pkg oz stove top stuffing mix for chicken cups cooked chicken diced i have used less oz frozen broccoli florets thawed drained can cream of chicken soup c milk c shredded cheddar cheese i prefer cheez whiz or velveeta preheat oven to ' prepare stuffing mix as directed on pkg set aside mix chicken and broccoli in baking dish stir in soup milk and cheese top with the prepared stuffing bake minutes or until cooked through the original recipe called for mayonnaise but i didnt have any on hand so i substituted ranch dressing i thought for sure that i ruined it but it was awesome and my family loved it classic herbed chicken envelope lipton recipe secrets savory herb with garlic soup mix tbsp water c of ranch dressing boneless chicken breast preheat oven to degrees in small bowl blend savory herb with garlic soup mix ranch dressing and water in baking pan sprayed with nonstick spray arrange chicken pour of soup mixture over chicken bake uncovered turning once and pour remaining soup mixture over chicken minutes or until chicken is no longer pink broccoli chicken casserole boiled chicken breasts diced into small chunks just boil the chicken for at least minutes or until no longer pink cool and then cut into chunks pkg broccoli can of cream of chicken pepperidge farm stuffing c mayonnaise tsp lemon juice oz pkg mild cheddar cheese boiled the broccoli for minutes then drain boiling the broccoli speeds up the cooking time combine soup mayonnaise and lemon juice mix with broccoli and diced chicken sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix bake at ' for minutes chicken and mushroom bake with rice chicken pieces c water can cream of mushroom or cream of celery soup i prefer cream of mushroom c rice medium carrots sliced i sometimes omit celery salt for seasoning paprika for seasoning tsp salt as needed place rice in bottom of a baking dish pour c water over rice add can mushroom soup stir to mix with rice place chicken pieces salted and peppered on top of rice mix sprinkle with celery salt add carrots add remaining c water to mushroom soup in can stir until well blended pour over chicken carrots and rice sprinkle paprika on top sometimes i add a little parsley nice pretty effect cover tightly with foil bake at ' for hour you can also cook this without the rice and carrots it makes a nice gravy to pour over cooked rice or noodles this is quick and easy a family favorite saturday chicken servings chicken pieces you dont have to use that many chicken pieces use how many pieces you want the rest of the recipe stays the same can condensed cream of mushroom or cream of chicken cup of cream dont cheat and use milk the cream makes a lot of difference i have cheated and used milk lol but the cream does taste better salt garlic powder and paprika to taste chopped parsley season chicken with salt garlic and paprika next spread it out in one layer baking pan dilute the soup with the cream pour it over the chicken and sprinkle parsley on top bake uncovered at ' for hour or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with fork makes a delicious gravy serve with mashed potatoes or buttered noodles or rice 